          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Reserve Component Employer Incentive, Compensation, and Relief Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a tax credit for certain employers of reservists (i.e., members of the National Guard or a reserve component of the Armed Forces). </p> <p>The tax credit is equal to $1,000 for each reservist employed during the year, plus an additional amount that ranges from $3,000 to $10,000, depending on the number of days the reservist serves in the uniformed services during the year. </p>]]></text>
